WEBVTT

00:00.120 --> 00:03.103
- <i>Previously on</i> Good Witch.
<i>- My dad used to bring me</i>

00:03.128 --> 00:04.795
<i>- gifts from his trips.
- Where?</i>

00:04.830 --> 00:06.730
<i>- London. That's the last time
I saw him.</i>

00:06.765 --> 00:08.432
<i>- The day that he left.
- She didn't say much,</i>

00:08.467 --> 00:10.734
but I could tell your daughter
was very happy to receive it.

00:10.769 --> 00:13.470
- I like to see you smile.
- You do?

00:13.505 --> 00:14.638
- Yeah.

00:14.673 --> 00:16.640
<i>- Who gave you that?
- Noah.</i>

00:16.675 --> 00:19.176
- That was nice of him.
- It was.

00:19.211 --> 00:21.945
- I love your mother very much.

00:21.981 --> 00:25.449
And I love you, and I wanted
to ask if it would be OK

00:25.484 --> 00:27.584
- if I married your mother.
- Yes.

00:27.620 --> 00:30.320
I'll get it.

00:34.860 --> 00:37.327
Dad...

00:37.363 --> 00:39.329
What are you doing here?

00:39.365 --> 00:41.498
- I wanted to see
my daughter.

00:41.533 --> 00:44.334
- It's been 22 years.

00:44.370 --> 00:46.336
- I know, Abby,
and when I left...

00:46.372 --> 00:48.972
- People call me Abigail now.

00:49.008 --> 00:50.440
- Abigail...

00:50.476 --> 00:53.810
of course. I've been thinking

00:53.846 --> 00:56.480
about what I wanted to say
to you for so long...

00:58.384 --> 01:01.378
but now, I... I don't know
where to begin.

01:08.227 --> 01:10.027
- What's going on?
- Who was at the door?

01:10.062 --> 01:13.363
I'm going to bed.

01:13.399 --> 01:16.033
- Everything OK?
- I don't know.

01:24.410 --> 01:27.311
<i>- Oh, there you go.
- Now you can eat here</i>

01:27.346 --> 01:29.413
or out in the garden.

01:32.418 --> 01:35.185
- Hey!
- Hey. Good morning.

01:35.220 --> 01:37.020
- Waffles?!
- Yeah.

01:37.056 --> 01:38.989
- I've seen fruit,
I've seen yogurt,

01:39.024 --> 01:41.091
- but I rarely have seen waffles.
- I am full of surprises.

01:41.126 --> 01:42.919
- Are they made with organic sweeteners

01:42.944 --> 01:44.895
and filled with some kind of wheat brand.

01:44.930 --> 01:48.065
- They are made with sugar
and filled with chocolate chips.

01:48.100 --> 01:50.067
- It is a surprise!
- Mm-hmm.

01:50.102 --> 01:51.902
- Hey, did you find out who came
to see Abigail last night?

01:51.937 --> 01:54.204
- No, and I haven't seen
her yet this morning.

01:54.239 --> 01:57.407
- Hmm. Is she OK?
- Yeah, she always seems to be,

01:57.443 --> 01:59.409
so she should be able
to handle the appearance

01:59.445 --> 02:02.579
- of one unexpected visitor.
- Morning!

02:02.614 --> 02:06.450
- Hey. Chocolate-chip waffles.
- Oooh!

02:06.485 --> 02:10.887
So, uh, I got an email about
the math competition finals.

02:10.923 --> 02:12.689
They're this weekend.

02:12.725 --> 02:15.258
I, uh, made it
into the regional championship.

02:15.294 --> 02:17.427
- Hey, congratulations!
- Grace, that's great!

02:17.463 --> 02:20.430
- Yeah. Uh, hey,
can you take me?

02:20.466 --> 02:23.100
- This weekend?
- Yeah, it's all day Saturday.

02:23.135 --> 02:25.936
- Actually, I have some guests
that I think are gonna need

02:25.971 --> 02:28.071
- some extra attention, but...
- I could take her.

02:28.107 --> 02:32.442
- Are you sure?
- I got all day free. Happy to.

02:32.478 --> 02:36.113
- OK. Uh, yeah. Great.

02:36.148 --> 02:38.782
- I will see you guys later.
- OK.

02:38.817 --> 02:40.550
- Bye!
- Bye.

02:40.586 --> 02:42.552
- Hey, I wanted one of those!
- These are for someone else,

02:42.588 --> 02:45.055
but there's plenty of fruit and yogurt.

02:45.090 --> 02:47.958
- But they're not filled
with chocolate chips.

02:54.199 --> 02:57.601
- Good morning. I was just
bringing this up to your room.

02:57.636 --> 03:01.571
- Chocolate-chip waffles. I used
to love those when I was a kid.

03:01.607 --> 03:04.141
- Did you?
- Uh, well, whoever came

03:04.176 --> 03:06.476
to see you last night
left this for you at the door.

03:07.296 --> 03:09.679
Has your name on the card.

03:12.518 --> 03:14.584
- It says "Abby"
on the card.

03:15.178 --> 03:16.486
- Yes.

03:16.522 --> 03:19.523
And I'm pretty sure I know
who used to call you that.

03:19.975 --> 03:23.660
- It's from my dad.
- I had a feeling.

03:23.695 --> 03:26.930
I didn't know he was even alive.

03:26.965 --> 03:30.500
- Yeah. It would probably be
easier if he wasn't.

03:31.194 --> 03:33.003
- Where has he been
all these years?

03:33.038 --> 03:36.306
- He didn't say
and I didn't ask.

03:39.745 --> 03:42.679
He wants me to meet him
for dinner tonight at 7.

03:44.049 --> 03:46.516
I don't show up,
I never have to see him again.

03:47.544 --> 03:49.453
- What are you gonna do?

